1
00:00:00,383 --> 00:00:02,752
(One autumn day with pretty autumn leaves around the school)

2
00:00:02,753 --> 00:00:04,452
- Oh, my.
- Let's go in.

3
00:00:04,453 --> 00:00:06,022
- Let's go.
- Hey, Kyung Hoon.

4
00:00:06,023 --> 00:00:08,362
- Kyung Hoon... Gosh, who is he?
- Who is he?

5
00:00:08,363 --> 00:00:10,392
- Why are you standing there?
- Don't mistake me for him.

6
00:00:10,393 --> 00:00:11,432
- I'm still young.
- You thought he was me, right?

7
00:00:11,433 --> 00:00:13,662
- Mimi Minu is the director?
- Come on. Kyung Hoon is here.

8
00:00:13,663 --> 00:00:15,172
- Is Mimi Minu the director?
- Hey, does that mean...

9
00:00:15,173 --> 00:00:17,532
that Shin Dong and Hee Chul will be absent again?

10
00:00:17,533 --> 00:00:19,342
- Oh, I guess that's right.
- Right. They're on a concert tour.

11
00:00:19,343 --> 00:00:21,072
Class president, are they absent? Or were they fired?

12
00:00:21,073 --> 00:00:22,342
- I bet they got fired.
- Were they fired?

13
00:00:22,343 --> 00:00:23,542
- This is nice.
- Oh, my. This is really...

14
00:00:23,543 --> 00:00:24,772
Since Mimi Minu is here, our classroom...

15
00:00:24,773 --> 00:00:26,743
Hot mamas, our dear queens.

16
00:00:27,113 --> 00:00:29,153
(Hot mamas, our dear queens.)

17
00:00:29,553 --> 00:00:32,082
- Hi!
- Oh, they're here.

18
00:00:32,083 --> 00:00:34,182
- Let's go!
- Oh, my. South America...

19
00:00:34,183 --> 00:00:35,692
- What are you guys doing?
- We were worried about you.

20
00:00:35,693 --> 00:00:37,552
I know, right? I haven't seen you in a long time.

21
00:00:37,553 --> 00:00:38,822
- It's been a really long time.
- Exactly.

22
00:00:38,823 --> 00:00:39,823
- It's been almost a month.
- One month.

23
00:00:39,824 --> 00:00:42,092
- Maybe because it's been a while...
- Maybe because it's been a while...

24
00:00:42,093 --> 00:00:44,532
- Why is Jong Shin sitting there?
- Exactly.

25
00:00:44,533 --> 00:00:46,462
- I thought I was on "Sing Again."
- We said the same thing last week.

26
00:00:46,463 --> 00:00:47,802
- Did you say that last week?
- We said that last week.

27
00:00:47,803 --> 00:00:49,432
- Yes, we did.
- Good job.

28
00:00:49,433 --> 00:00:51,172
- He was on "No Back Tak Jae Hoon."
- Everyone.

29
00:00:51,173 --> 00:00:52,672
Settle down, everyone.

30
00:00:52,673 --> 00:00:55,512
I heard that we started to make a class newspaper last week.

31
00:00:55,513 --> 00:00:57,642
MIYEON, who's a member of the newspaper club, came...

32
00:00:57,643 --> 00:00:59,112
- and helped us make one.
- Call MIYEON here.

33
00:00:59,113 --> 00:01:00,812
- Not only about us...
- She came last week,

34
00:01:00,813 --> 00:01:02,652
- and we made a class newspaper.
- I see.

35
00:01:02,653 --> 00:01:04,512
Share what's new with you.

36
00:01:04,513 --> 00:01:05,752
Even trivial things will do.

37
00:01:05,753 --> 00:01:06,922
There was something that surprised me.

38
00:01:06,923 --> 00:01:09,952
- MIYEON came on the show recently.
- Yes, she did.

39
00:01:09,953 --> 00:01:11,422
Before shooting that episode,

40
00:01:11,423 --> 00:01:14,123
MIYEON shot a video for my YouTube channel.

41
00:01:14,423 --> 00:01:18,463
(MIYEON appeared in a video on Mimi Minu's YouTube channel.)

42
00:01:18,903 --> 00:01:22,303
(The crazy combination of Mimi Minu and MIYEON)

43
00:01:22,503 --> 00:01:25,343
Our challenge video will have been uploaded before this airs.

44
00:01:25,603 --> 00:01:29,773
(They also made a "Say My Name" challenge video.)

45
00:01:29,813 --> 00:01:31,842
How was her new song?

46
00:01:31,843 --> 00:01:34,712
MIYEON used to sing cheerful songs.

47
00:01:34,713 --> 00:01:37,252
But her new song has a dark, gloomy vibe.

48
00:01:37,253 --> 00:01:38,253
What's the song title?

49
00:01:38,254 --> 00:01:40,882
"Say My Name" is the title track.

50
00:01:40,883 --> 00:01:42,352
- "Say My Name."
- Oh, that's correct.

51
00:01:42,353 --> 00:01:43,592
- "Say My Name?"
- That's right.

52
00:01:43,593 --> 00:01:45,062
- He remembered it.
- I remembered it accurately.

53
00:01:45,063 --> 00:01:46,962
- That was close, right?
- Yes, that was close.

54
00:01:46,963 --> 00:01:48,192
We should write that Mimi Minu said...

55
00:01:48,193 --> 00:01:49,432
that MIYEON's new song was dreary.

56
00:01:49,433 --> 00:01:50,433
- No, that's not right.
- He said MIYEON's new song...

57
00:01:50,434 --> 00:01:51,832
- was gloomy.
- Are you really writing that?

58
00:01:51,833 --> 00:01:53,062
"Mimi Minu Says MIYEON's New Song Is Not Cheerful."

59
00:01:53,063 --> 00:01:55,272
- "MIYEON's Song Is Gloomy."
- "Gloomy."

60
00:01:55,273 --> 00:01:57,072
- Hey, this is...
- A news article...

61
00:01:57,073 --> 00:01:58,842
- doesn't have to be like that.
- I've never heard "gloomy."

62
00:01:58,843 --> 00:02:01,002
- Oh, "Rose."
- I have a story to tell.

63
00:02:01,003 --> 00:02:03,242
- A few days ago, - Yes?

64
00:02:03,243 --> 00:02:05,442
I went to the Philippines to shoot my basketball show.

65
00:02:05,443 --> 00:02:07,042
Right. The game was held at the SM Mall of Asia Arena.

66
00:02:07,043 --> 00:02:08,482
- A sports arena in the Philippines.
- Yes, that's right.

67
00:02:08,483 --> 00:02:10,412
I found out something very surprising.

68
00:02:10,413 --> 00:02:12,953
- Men on a Mission...
- We didn't go on the show.

69
00:02:13,283 --> 00:02:16,652
- is on OTT in the Philippines...
- Okay.

70
00:02:16,653 --> 00:02:18,223
with English subtitles.

71
00:02:19,163 --> 00:02:20,163
Really?

72
00:02:20,164 --> 00:02:21,962
- So I... Can you guys...
- It's not on the Korean platform.

73
00:02:21,963 --> 00:02:23,262
- Hold on.
- I heard it was aired in Japan.

74
00:02:23,263 --> 00:02:24,963
- Yes, it's aired in Japan too.
- In Japan as well.

75
00:02:25,333 --> 00:02:29,132
Only a few of Korean variety shows are on the Philippines' OTT.

76
00:02:29,133 --> 00:02:31,032
And the translated version of Men on a Mission is streamed...

77
00:02:31,033 --> 00:02:32,442
in the Philippines.

78
00:02:32,443 --> 00:02:34,702
Let's write this. "Seo Jang Hoon Becomes..."

79
00:02:34,703 --> 00:02:36,642
- No, wait. Hold on.
- "Popular in the Philippines."

80
00:02:36,643 --> 00:02:38,172
- No, that's not what I mean.
- That's random.

81
00:02:38,173 --> 00:02:40,542
"Seo Jang Hoon Is As Popular As Sandara Park in the Philippines."

82
00:02:40,543 --> 00:02:42,412
- Okay.
- No, it's not like that.

83
00:02:42,413 --> 00:02:44,512
- Everyone, hear me out.
- "As Popular As Pacquiao."

84
00:02:44,513 --> 00:02:46,182
- "Seo Jang Hoon Has..."
- Pacquiao came on the show before.

85
00:02:46,183 --> 00:02:47,952
- Oh, that's right.
- "Fighting Match against Pacquiao."

86
00:02:47,953 --> 00:02:48,953
- I...
- My gosh.

87
00:02:49,193 --> 00:02:50,652
- "In the Philippines, Jang Hoon..."
- Hear me out.

88
00:02:50,653 --> 00:02:52,222
- "Challenges Pacquiao To Match."
- I...

89
00:02:52,223 --> 00:02:54,162
- He asked us to hear him out.
- Don't write anything yet.

90
00:02:54,163 --> 00:02:55,192
- He asked not to write it down.
- Don't write it yet.

91
00:02:55,193 --> 00:02:57,632
"Seo Jang Hoon Has Fighting Match against Pacquiao."

92
00:02:57,633 --> 00:02:58,862
- No, that's not true.
- "Picky Seo Jang Hoon..."

93
00:02:58,863 --> 00:03:00,063
"Starts Learning Pigalog."

94
00:03:00,233 --> 00:03:02,672
(Unexpected news, "Picky Jang Hoon Starts Learning Tagalog")

95
00:03:02,673 --> 00:03:03,673
He said "Pigalog," not "Tagalog."

96
00:03:04,033 --> 00:03:05,043
Did you say "Pigalog?"

97
00:03:05,373 --> 00:03:07,742
- Anyway, I found that out, - He started learning Tagalog?

98
00:03:07,743 --> 00:03:09,072
- and that surprised me.
- Right.

99
00:03:09,073 --> 00:03:11,682
Men on a Mission is streamed in the Philippines...

100
00:03:11,683 --> 00:03:14,542
- Amid popular acclaim.
- amid popular acclaim.

101
00:03:14,543 --> 00:03:16,412
- I'm really grateful.
- The viewers in the Philippines,

102
00:03:16,413 --> 00:03:17,552
- Put it in the end.
- thank you.

103
00:03:17,553 --> 00:03:19,722
- And Soo Geun.
- I just remembered a story to tell.

104
00:03:19,723 --> 00:03:21,552
We've been holding a 20th anniversary concert tour.

105
00:03:21,553 --> 00:03:24,092
To celebrate the 20th anniversary of Super Junior,

106
00:03:24,093 --> 00:03:26,192
I wanted to do something to repay our fans for their support.

107
00:03:26,193 --> 00:03:28,893
So I secretly made a donation to help cancer patients.

108
00:03:29,963 --> 00:03:31,132
- But...
- Secretly?

109
00:03:31,133 --> 00:03:33,402
But I don't want it to be a secret, so I'm sharing the news.

110
00:03:33,403 --> 00:03:36,102
- What's that?
- That's so great of you.

111
00:03:36,103 --> 00:03:37,672
- Indeed.
- What's that?

112
00:03:37,673 --> 00:03:40,142
- He donated to cancer patients.
- "Kim Hee Chul..."

113
00:03:40,143 --> 00:03:41,572
"Kim Hee Chul Openly Makes Donation."

114
00:03:41,573 --> 00:03:42,712
- Exactly.
- It's not a secret anymore.

115
00:03:42,713 --> 00:03:44,012
- I mean, it's really great of him.
- But he said...

116
00:03:44,013 --> 00:03:45,013
I wrote that I had made a donation and bragged about it.

117
00:03:45,014 --> 00:03:47,412
- It's still a great thing to do.
- Right. It's a good deed.

118
00:03:47,413 --> 00:03:50,682
I counted the number of episodes of our show.

119
00:03:50,683 --> 00:03:51,982
This is our 506th episode.

120
00:03:51,983 --> 00:03:53,622
- Yes, it's been that long.
- That's amazing.

121
00:03:53,623 --> 00:03:55,853
To tell you the truth, in the past 506 weeks,

122
00:03:56,253 --> 00:03:57,892
I had naengmyeon every single week.

123
00:03:57,893 --> 00:03:59,222
- What did you say?
- "Kang Ho Dong..."

124
00:03:59,223 --> 00:04:01,192
- For 506 weeks, - "Kang Ho Dong..."

125
00:04:01,193 --> 00:04:02,893
- I ate Pyongyang naengmyeon.
- Unbelievable.

126
00:04:03,293 --> 00:04:04,792
"Kang Ho Dong Is from Pyongyang."

127
00:04:04,793 --> 00:04:05,832
- Hang on.
- "Love for Pyongyang naengmyeon."

128
00:04:05,833 --> 00:04:07,802
- "Turns Out To Be from Pyongyang."
- He was born in Pyongyang.

129
00:04:07,803 --> 00:04:10,032
- For 506 weeks...
- We should check it out.

130
00:04:10,033 --> 00:04:12,042
Don't you think he should get into the Guinness World Records?

131
00:04:12,043 --> 00:04:13,072
- It's really unbelievable.
- "Kang Ho Dong..."

132
00:04:13,073 --> 00:04:15,242
- He ate it for 506 weeks.
- He could set a world record.

133
00:04:15,243 --> 00:04:17,272
"Kang Ho Dong Has Pyongyang Naengmyeon for 506 Weeks,"

134
00:04:17,273 --> 00:04:18,682
"Will He Move to Pyongyang?"

135
00:04:18,683 --> 00:04:20,812
I recently saw Soo Geun in a video.

136
00:04:20,813 --> 00:04:22,912
- It was a teaser.
- "Three Idiots in Kenya."

137
00:04:22,913 --> 00:04:25,622
- Yes, I saw him in the teaser.
- It's on OTT.

138
00:04:25,623 --> 00:04:27,853
- He gave a giraffe physical touch.
- That's right.

139
00:04:28,283 --> 00:04:30,652
- "He Gives Giraffe Physical Touch."
- On that day..

140
00:04:30,653 --> 00:04:31,892
- "Giraffe..."
- "Their Tongues Touch."

141
00:04:31,893 --> 00:04:33,062
I pecked a giraffe,

142
00:04:33,063 --> 00:04:34,923
and that evening, the giraffe came into my room.

143
00:04:35,593 --> 00:04:38,292
"Soo Geun Dyes His Hair with Squid Ink."

144
00:04:38,293 --> 00:04:40,062
- "Soo Geun Sleeps with Giraffe."
- Write that he dyed his hair.

145
00:04:40,063 --> 00:04:41,402
"Giraffe Ten Times Taller Than Soo Geun."

146
00:04:41,403 --> 00:04:42,972
- Because he dyed his hair...
- All right.

147
00:04:42,973 --> 00:04:44,502
- "Dyes His Hair with Squid Ink..."
- Jang Hoon likes the joke.

148
00:04:44,503 --> 00:04:46,042
"And with Giraffe..."

149
00:04:46,043 --> 00:04:47,172
- "First Night with Giraffe."
- "Soo Geun Kisses Giraffe."

150
00:04:47,173 --> 00:04:48,772
"Soo Geun Turns Out To Be Ten Times Shorter Than Giraffe."

151
00:04:48,773 --> 00:04:50,142
"Soo Geun Meets Giraffe Secretly."

152
00:04:50,143 --> 00:04:51,143
"With Giraffe..."

153
00:04:51,144 --> 00:04:52,512
("Lee Soo Geun Says He Becomes Interested in Anything Tall")

154
00:04:52,513 --> 00:04:53,642
This is fun.

155
00:04:53,643 --> 00:04:54,982
So he likes tall people.

156
00:04:54,983 --> 00:04:57,883
I renewed my contract with my agency.

157
00:04:58,253 --> 00:05:00,352
- What? Really?
- It's been almost ten years...

158
00:05:00,353 --> 00:05:02,152
- "The Loyal Min Kyung Hoon?"
- since I started working with them.

159
00:05:02,153 --> 00:05:04,422
- Write something like that.
- Apparently, you are...

160
00:05:04,423 --> 00:05:06,292
the only active celebrity at your agency.

161
00:05:06,293 --> 00:05:08,023
That's why I keep renewing my contract.

162
00:05:08,633 --> 00:05:10,162
"Kyung Hoon Does Men on a Mission for Ten Years..."

163
00:05:10,163 --> 00:05:11,293
"And Works with Same Agency for Ten Years."

164
00:05:11,733 --> 00:05:12,803
That's true.

165
00:05:12,963 --> 00:05:14,262
- Can't we get these articles...
- It's very loyal of him.

166
00:05:14,263 --> 00:05:15,803
published in JoongAng Ilbo?

167
00:05:16,503 --> 00:05:18,872
I hope we can get them published in JoongAng Ilbo.

168
00:05:18,873 --> 00:05:20,272
- That'd be great.
- Right.

169
00:05:20,273 --> 00:05:21,602
It'd be helpful for us even if only a few of them get published.

170
00:05:21,603 --> 00:05:23,243
- I'll change the expression.
- Aren't they back?

171
00:05:23,743 --> 00:05:24,743
Hey, guys.

172
00:05:25,613 --> 00:05:26,613
Hey, guys.

173
00:05:27,343 --> 00:05:29,753
Write some articles about us too.

174
00:05:30,283 --> 00:05:32,352
- SUNMI!
- It's good to see you again.

175
00:05:32,353 --> 00:05:33,722
- Hello.
- You're here, Chan Won.

176
00:05:33,723 --> 00:05:34,882
Song Min Jun!

177
00:05:34,883 --> 00:05:36,853
We met him when we shot the 500th episode.

178
00:05:37,753 --> 00:05:40,162
- He came to celebrate with us.
- SUNMI's hair color is elegant now.

179
00:05:40,163 --> 00:05:41,492
He came on the show to congratulate us.

180
00:05:41,493 --> 00:05:43,092
- Yes, for the 500th episode.
- We thank you for that.

181
00:05:43,093 --> 00:05:44,763
Which school did you guys transfer from?

182
00:05:45,403 --> 00:05:46,562
- We are...
- Yes.

183
00:05:46,563 --> 00:05:48,703
from Doing Fine As Solo Artists High School.

184
00:05:49,203 --> 00:05:51,572
I'm SUNMI. I made my comeback as a virgin ghost.

185
00:05:51,573 --> 00:05:52,672
- And?
- It must be her title track.

186
00:05:52,673 --> 00:05:55,672
I contributed a little to getting the highest ratings...

187
00:05:55,673 --> 00:05:57,242
in Men on a Mission history. I'm Chan Won.

188
00:05:57,243 --> 00:05:58,243
Chan Won!

189
00:05:58,244 --> 00:06:00,183
I'm the nobleman-like trot singer Min Jun. It's nice to meet you.

190
00:06:00,713 --> 00:06:01,713
Min Jun!

191
00:06:01,714 --> 00:06:03,082
(Welcome, all of you!)

192
00:06:03,083 --> 00:06:04,882
SUNMI made her comeback as a virgin ghost?

193
00:06:04,883 --> 00:06:06,722
- It must be her new song.
- A virgin ghost?

194
00:06:06,723 --> 00:06:07,852
- Yes, I'm a virgin ghost.
- Oh, my.

195
00:06:07,853 --> 00:06:09,352
SUNMI, I haven't seen you in a really long time.

196
00:06:09,353 --> 00:06:10,622
I missed you.

197
00:06:10,623 --> 00:06:11,692
- How long has it been?
- You're lying.

198
00:06:11,693 --> 00:06:12,992
- Stop lying.
- I mean it. I missed him.

199
00:06:12,993 --> 00:06:14,692
How much did you miss Ho Dong?

200
00:06:14,693 --> 00:06:17,032
- I really missed him.
- When did you last meet him?

201
00:06:17,033 --> 00:06:18,432
- I think she means it.
- It's because...

202
00:06:18,433 --> 00:06:20,432
- It's been about four years.
- Four or five years?

203
00:06:20,433 --> 00:06:21,433
- It's been four or five years.
- That long?

204
00:06:21,903 --> 00:06:24,933
(SUNMI, the most beautiful one of all)

205
00:06:26,073 --> 00:06:30,412
(SUNMI performed "Pporappippam" spreading beauty 5 years ago.)

206
00:06:30,413 --> 00:06:32,213
By the way, SUNMI...

207
00:06:32,713 --> 00:06:34,282
Shin Dong wasn't here when you came on the show, right?

208
00:06:34,283 --> 00:06:36,882
I think I appeared only in Part Two when she came on the show.

209
00:06:36,883 --> 00:06:39,382
She's never been here since I started being in Part One.

210
00:06:39,383 --> 00:06:40,582
- Here's why I said that.
- That's right.

211
00:06:40,583 --> 00:06:42,122
I saw a photo of them...

212
00:06:42,123 --> 00:06:44,752
and found out that they were trained in the same period of time.

213
00:06:44,753 --> 00:06:47,022
- That's true.
- We auditioned in the same year.

214
00:06:47,023 --> 00:06:48,662
- For what agency? SM Entertainment?
- SM Entertainment.

215
00:06:48,663 --> 00:06:50,962
One of the two of them...

216
00:06:50,963 --> 00:06:54,462
was going to be the last member to join Super Junior.

217
00:06:54,463 --> 00:06:56,033
And sadly, Shin Dong was chosen.

218
00:06:56,603 --> 00:06:58,672
- She could've debuted then.
- She wasn't chosen as a member?

219
00:06:58,673 --> 00:07:00,342
- That's right.
- I'm sorry to SUNMI.

220
00:07:00,343 --> 00:07:03,473
I came in first place at the audition.

221
00:07:04,073 --> 00:07:06,042
So I was hired...

222
00:07:06,043 --> 00:07:07,812
- and debuted.
- That's right.

223
00:07:07,813 --> 00:07:10,282
As for SUNMI, the casting team of JYP Entertainment...

224
00:07:10,283 --> 00:07:11,882
- hired her.
- That's right.

225
00:07:11,883 --> 00:07:13,822
- Had SUNMI came in first place, - Why...

226
00:07:13,823 --> 00:07:14,982
would SUNMI have become a member of Super Junior...

227
00:07:14,983 --> 00:07:16,052
and would Shin Dong have...

228
00:07:16,053 --> 00:07:17,122
- joined Wonder Girls?
- That's right.

229
00:07:17,123 --> 00:07:18,592
My gosh. What a shame.

230
00:07:18,593 --> 00:07:19,892
- That would've been interesting.
- Exactly.

231
00:07:19,893 --> 00:07:22,992
I wonder why they made that decision.

232
00:07:22,993 --> 00:07:24,762
- At the time...
- You mean, SM Entertainment?

233
00:07:24,763 --> 00:07:27,962
While Shin Dong and I were preparing for the audition...

234
00:07:27,963 --> 00:07:30,302
There was a burger place in the neighborhood, remember?

235
00:07:30,303 --> 00:07:31,602
- McDonalds.
- You remember that?

236
00:07:31,603 --> 00:07:33,602
- Of course. We went there together.
- What?

237
00:07:33,603 --> 00:07:35,442
- Back then, - You mean, 20 years ago?

238
00:07:35,443 --> 00:07:38,142
SUNMI was... Were you in 6th or 7th grade?

239
00:07:38,143 --> 00:07:39,212
- I was in sixth grade.
- Seventh grade?

240
00:07:39,213 --> 00:07:40,282
She was in sixth grade,

241
00:07:40,283 --> 00:07:41,842
- and I was 20.
- She was so young.

242
00:07:41,843 --> 00:07:43,982
Since I was the oldest trainee,

243
00:07:43,983 --> 00:07:45,882
I walked the younger trainees to the subway station.

244
00:07:45,883 --> 00:07:47,152
That's right.

245
00:07:47,153 --> 00:07:49,422
There were some other trainees other than SUNMI.

246
00:07:49,423 --> 00:07:51,962
We were hungry on our way, so we went to the burger place.

247
00:07:51,963 --> 00:07:53,422
- We ate burgers there.
- That's nice of you.

248
00:07:53,423 --> 00:07:54,862
- That's really nice.
- Were they hungry too?

249
00:07:54,863 --> 00:07:56,132
- Or were you the hungry one?
- That's a heartwarming story.

250
00:07:56,133 --> 00:07:57,963
I'm sure I was the one who was hungry since I suggested the idea.

251
00:07:59,663 --> 00:08:01,232
- So Shin Dong placed first?
- He's so nice.

252
00:08:01,233 --> 00:08:04,003
Exactly. Shin Dong placed first at the audition.

253
00:08:04,233 --> 00:08:07,572
- He was chosen as the funniest one.
- That's right.

254
00:08:07,573 --> 00:08:10,613
- But I still don't understand...
- That makes sense.

255
00:08:11,073 --> 00:08:12,212
- I mean...
- Why Shin Dong placed first?

256
00:08:12,213 --> 00:08:13,913
His performance wasn't funny enough to place first.

257
00:08:15,313 --> 00:08:16,712
- You placed first by being funny?
- What kind of performance was it?

258
00:08:16,713 --> 00:08:17,912
- Yes.
- I'll explain to you.

259
00:08:17,913 --> 00:08:20,022
There were several categories.

260
00:08:20,023 --> 00:08:22,792
There were categories of appearance, singing,

261
00:08:22,793 --> 00:08:24,522
and dancing as well. And I applied...

262
00:08:24,523 --> 00:08:26,292
- for the dancing category.
- That's right.

263
00:08:26,293 --> 00:08:28,622
But the people at the agency said...

264
00:08:28,623 --> 00:08:30,162
that I would be a better fit for the funny category...

265
00:08:30,163 --> 00:08:31,732
and advised me to apply for that category.

266
00:08:31,733 --> 00:08:34,632
- Tin Tin Five was active then.
- They were popular back then.

267
00:08:34,633 --> 00:08:37,673
The agency was planning to form the next Tin Tin Five.

268
00:08:38,073 --> 00:08:39,842
There was such a rumor.

269
00:08:39,843 --> 00:08:41,902
But that plan fell through, and I joined Super Junior.

270
00:08:41,903 --> 00:08:45,383
But that's not important. Right now, we...

271
00:08:45,613 --> 00:08:47,382
- But Shin Dong was telling us...
- Why...

272
00:08:47,383 --> 00:08:49,782
- Why is it not important?
- So you were chosen.

273
00:08:49,783 --> 00:08:51,582
- Why?
- It's about SUNMI, not you.

274
00:08:51,583 --> 00:08:54,682
- So you placed first, right?
- Yes, that's right.

275
00:08:54,683 --> 00:08:58,152
The point is that they didn't pick SUNMI.

276
00:08:58,153 --> 00:09:00,722
- That's right.
- SUNMI was very young back then,

277
00:09:00,723 --> 00:09:01,723
and she was shy.

278
00:09:01,724 --> 00:09:03,162
- That's true.
- Right. I have no doubt.

279
00:09:03,163 --> 00:09:04,563
- Shin Dong, seriously...
- But that's not important.

280
00:09:04,763 --> 00:09:06,502
- Right.
- Why is it not important?

281
00:09:06,503 --> 00:09:07,562
- Why is it not important?
- He said it wasn't important.

282
00:09:07,563 --> 00:09:10,102
- It's not the time...
- I think this will be edited out.

283
00:09:10,103 --> 00:09:13,772
- for us to talk about it.
- I agree.

284
00:09:13,773 --> 00:09:16,612
We all owe Chan Won the biggest apology.

285
00:09:16,613 --> 00:09:17,712
- Why?
- Why?

286
00:09:17,713 --> 00:09:19,842
We're supposed to be too ashamed to see him.

287
00:09:19,843 --> 00:09:21,042
- We should all lower our heads.
- Why?

288
00:09:21,043 --> 00:09:22,252
- Why?
- Why are you sorry to me?

289
00:09:22,253 --> 00:09:24,452
- We should lower our heads?
- Chan Won came on the show...

290
00:09:24,453 --> 00:09:26,283
- to celebrate the 500th episode.
- Yes.

291
00:09:27,083 --> 00:09:30,693
(Chan Won came as a special guest for the 500th episode.)

292
00:09:32,693 --> 00:09:37,393
(He celebrated the 500th episode by performing "Jinttobaegi.")

293
00:09:37,493 --> 00:09:39,563
He performed a song and did an interview.

294
00:09:40,003 --> 00:09:42,433
- But his interview was edited out.
- Really?

295
00:09:42,503 --> 00:09:43,633
It was because of Yeong Cheol.

296
00:09:45,173 --> 00:09:46,372
- I'm sorry.
- He gave a touching performance...

297
00:09:46,373 --> 00:09:48,813
- which was totally unexpected.
- I performed well.

298
00:09:49,513 --> 00:09:53,683
(Yeong Cheol performed "Golden," which was unexpectedly touching.)

299
00:09:55,213 --> 00:09:57,613
(Even Ho Dong got teary.)

300
00:09:57,783 --> 00:10:00,053
- I tried too hard...
- He performed unnecessarily well.

301
00:10:00,153 --> 00:10:01,523
- He made Chan Won...
- He sang well, indeed.

302
00:10:01,653 --> 00:10:04,023
That part where he was interviewed was edited out.

303
00:10:04,093 --> 00:10:05,693
- The whole part was edited out?
- We must have the footage.

304
00:10:05,723 --> 00:10:07,762
My interview was edited out.

305
00:10:07,763 --> 00:10:09,663
Moreover, my performance was also edited out after the first verse.

306
00:10:10,393 --> 00:10:13,162
- What?
- My whole performance was aired.

307
00:10:13,163 --> 00:10:14,862
- - You must've been...
- The whole performance.

308
00:10:14,863 --> 00:10:16,372
- surprised to find out about it...
- The interview wasn't aired.

309
00:10:16,373 --> 00:10:17,832
while watching the episode on TV.

310
00:10:17,833 --> 00:10:18,872
- I was surprised.
- That day...

311
00:10:18,873 --> 00:10:20,042
- I can't believe they cut it out.
- It was indeed surprising.

312
00:10:20,043 --> 00:10:21,602
- That's it.
- I guess we have the footage.

313
00:10:21,603 --> 00:10:23,073
- There wasn't enough time left.
- Oh, they have the footage.

314
00:10:23,413 --> 00:10:25,782
(I realized that Men on a Mission is still loved...)

315
00:10:25,783 --> 00:10:27,612
(by many people.)

316
00:10:27,613 --> 00:10:28,953
(I'd like to congratulate all of you.)

317
00:10:29,453 --> 00:10:32,352
(I believe the show has been gaining so much love...)

318
00:10:32,353 --> 00:10:35,652
(because the cast members maintained their chemistry.)

319
00:10:35,653 --> 00:10:37,353
(Also, they never lose the beginner's mindset.)

320
00:10:37,623 --> 00:10:40,863
(Chan Won showed his affection for Men on a Mission.)

321
00:10:41,063 --> 00:10:42,762
(It's good that we got to see the important interview.)

322
00:10:42,763 --> 00:10:43,992
My, thank you, Chan Won.

323
00:10:43,993 --> 00:10:45,532
So that interview wasn't aired.

324
00:10:45,533 --> 00:10:47,402
- Because of Yeong Cheol.
- He made a lot of good comments.

325
00:10:47,403 --> 00:10:49,533
You can see that he wasn't here...

326
00:10:49,633 --> 00:10:51,703
just as a guest singer.

327
00:10:51,803 --> 00:10:54,173
You can feel his genuine love for our show.

328
00:10:54,673 --> 00:10:58,372
I love all of the cast members,

329
00:10:58,373 --> 00:11:01,442
but one of them is my role model.

330
00:11:01,443 --> 00:11:04,982
He changed my life. He's Ho Dong.

331
00:11:04,983 --> 00:11:05,983
(Ho Dong is the member who changed Chan Won's life.)

332
00:11:05,984 --> 00:11:07,552
- Really? What did he do for you?
- I'm flattered.

333
00:11:07,553 --> 00:11:09,093
- That's...
- That's not important.

334
00:11:09,893 --> 00:11:11,053
That's not important?

335
00:11:11,393 --> 00:11:12,622
- It is important!
- It's not important.

336
00:11:12,623 --> 00:11:14,492
- How did he change your life?
- Why does that matter?

337
00:11:14,493 --> 00:11:16,162
- Take your time to tell us.
- Why does that matter?

338
00:11:16,163 --> 00:11:18,363
- It's an important story.
- That's not important.

339
00:11:18,493 --> 00:11:21,102
- Let's really focus on his story.
- What TV shows changed your life?

340
00:11:21,103 --> 00:11:23,172
- He changed someone else's life.
- Let's focus on it.

341
00:11:23,173 --> 00:11:25,002
- Hey, Chan Won.
- Yes?

342
00:11:25,003 --> 00:11:26,702
- It doesn't matter. What are...
- Okay.

343
00:11:26,703 --> 00:11:28,402
- the two life-changing shows?
- Let's focus on listening to him.

344
00:11:28,403 --> 00:11:29,672
- What shows changed your life?
- I'm curious about it.

345
00:11:29,673 --> 00:11:31,642
There have been two TV shows...

346
00:11:31,643 --> 00:11:33,583
- that changed my life.
- What are those?

347
00:11:34,013 --> 00:11:36,382
First, as you all must know,

348
00:11:36,383 --> 00:11:37,652
- "Mister Trot."
- Right.

349
00:11:37,653 --> 00:11:39,183
And the other one is...

350
00:11:39,323 --> 00:11:40,722
"Star King" where I appeared...

351
00:11:40,723 --> 00:11:42,122
- about 20 years ago.
- Oh, my goodness.

352
00:11:42,123 --> 00:11:43,953
Come on. That's not important. The third show...

353
00:11:44,253 --> 00:11:45,352
("Star King" is not important.)

354
00:11:45,353 --> 00:11:46,422
- We...
- "Star King..."

355
00:11:46,423 --> 00:11:48,493
- I went on the show three times.
- He said it didn't matter.

356
00:11:48,793 --> 00:11:51,932
- It was an honor to get a chance...
- Really?

357
00:11:51,933 --> 00:11:53,902
- to work with Ho Dong three times.
- I didn't know that.

358
00:11:53,903 --> 00:11:54,932
(Chan Won appeared on "Star King" three times as a trot prodigy.)

359
00:11:54,933 --> 00:11:57,202
- He came on the show as a prodigy.
- As a prodigy?

360
00:11:57,203 --> 00:11:58,973
I'll tell you how much it affected my life.

361
00:11:59,373 --> 00:12:01,603
Because of my loyalty to "Star King,"

362
00:12:01,703 --> 00:12:04,572
I never watched "Infinite Challenge" on time.

363
00:12:04,573 --> 00:12:06,413
- The shows aired at the same time.
- Yes, at the same time.

364
00:12:06,783 --> 00:12:09,212
I watched "Star King" on time every Saturday.

365
00:12:09,213 --> 00:12:10,213
For how long?

366
00:12:10,553 --> 00:12:12,383
Until "Star King" ended airing.

367
00:12:12,923 --> 00:12:15,423
- But I...
- You were there as a prodigy.

368
00:12:15,523 --> 00:12:17,392
- Ho Dong must've complimented you.
- Yes.

369
00:12:17,393 --> 00:12:18,792
SUNMI, you've been on the show...

370
00:12:18,793 --> 00:12:20,192
- as a guest, haven't you?
- Of course, sir.

371
00:12:20,193 --> 00:12:21,522
- No, I mean...
- See?

372
00:12:21,523 --> 00:12:23,162
- I mean, of course.
- We all were traumatized.

373
00:12:23,163 --> 00:12:25,232
- She spoke formally right away.
- The thought of "Star King..."

374
00:12:25,233 --> 00:12:26,233
makes us shudder.

375
00:12:27,033 --> 00:12:28,132
It makes her shudder.

376
00:12:28,133 --> 00:12:29,173
Does it mean she's terrified?

377
00:12:29,333 --> 00:12:30,772
- It makes her shudder.
- Even now?

378
00:12:30,773 --> 00:12:32,003
- Even now.
- It was recorded every Monday.

379
00:12:32,443 --> 00:12:34,143
The shoot started at noon on Mondays.

380
00:12:34,403 --> 00:12:37,942
But I heard that one of our guests suffered damage...

381
00:12:37,943 --> 00:12:39,412
because of Yeong Cheol, not Ho Dong.

382
00:12:39,413 --> 00:12:40,683
- What?
- One of them?

383
00:12:40,983 --> 00:12:42,482
- Because of Yeong Cheol?
- It must be SUNMI.

384
00:12:42,483 --> 00:12:43,682
It's not me.

385
00:12:43,683 --> 00:12:45,952
- I'm the one who suffered damage.
- Why?

386
00:12:45,953 --> 00:12:47,982
- I suffered serious damage.
- What happened?

387
00:12:47,983 --> 00:12:49,792
- It must've been financial damage.
- He must know.

388
00:12:49,793 --> 00:12:51,922
- The time has come.
- He'll finally be destroyed.

389
00:12:51,923 --> 00:12:53,462
It's about time we heard such a story.

390
00:12:53,463 --> 00:12:54,463
- Right.
- It's about time?

391
00:12:54,464 --> 00:12:56,062
Both Yeong Cheol and I appeared on...

392
00:12:56,063 --> 00:12:57,663
- "The King of Active Trot Singers."
- Gosh, not again.

393
00:12:58,393 --> 00:13:00,932
- I wish I hadn't been on that show.
- He was on the show as a comedian.

394
00:13:00,933 --> 00:13:03,602
Yeong Cheol performed right before me.

395
00:13:03,603 --> 00:13:05,173
I was going to perform after his performance.

396
00:13:05,273 --> 00:13:06,742
- Singing after a comedian is hard.
- Yeong Cheol...

397
00:13:06,743 --> 00:13:08,443
- That's funny.
- He got the lowest score.

398
00:13:08,843 --> 00:13:10,142
- Yeong Cheol did?
- He got the lowest score ever.

399
00:13:10,143 --> 00:13:11,942
Yeong Cheol got the lowest score.

400
00:13:11,943 --> 00:13:13,943
- So he became genuinely upset.
- He got some points?

401
00:13:14,443 --> 00:13:16,752
- My gosh.
- After his performance,

402
00:13:16,753 --> 00:13:17,982
he never pressed the button.

403
00:13:17,983 --> 00:13:19,122
My gosh. I can't believe him.

404
00:13:19,123 --> 00:13:20,482
He went on a power trip.

405
00:13:20,483 --> 00:13:21,882
The other singers evaluated one another.

406
00:13:21,883 --> 00:13:23,253
The contestants cast a vote for one another.

407
00:13:23,323 --> 00:13:24,552
It was called the peer evaluation round.

408
00:13:24,553 --> 00:13:27,493
Yeong Cheol acts quite timid on Men on a Mission, right?

409
00:13:27,593 --> 00:13:29,892
- He's like a thug on other shows.
- He's so confident on other shows.

410
00:13:29,893 --> 00:13:32,403
He uses his work experience in the TV industry as a weapon...

411
00:13:32,703 --> 00:13:35,363
Min Jun, you were right. I was upset.

412
00:13:35,803 --> 00:13:37,933
- He rarely pressed the button...
- Let me explain.

413
00:13:38,033 --> 00:13:39,443
I got 16 votes.

414
00:13:39,873 --> 00:13:41,742
- It broke me mentally.
- Weren't you supposed...

415
00:13:41,743 --> 00:13:43,573
to be grateful toward those 16 people?

416
00:13:43,873 --> 00:13:45,613
- You got more votes than I thought.
- Gosh, come on.

417
00:13:45,683 --> 00:13:47,042
- Sixteen votes are a lot.
- No, sixteen votes...

418
00:13:47,043 --> 00:13:49,113
- I was 1 of those 16 people.
- Min Jun...

419
00:13:49,183 --> 00:13:50,652
- Oh, you pressed the button?
- I pressed the button.

420
00:13:50,653 --> 00:13:52,783
- I even danced.
- You pressed the button?

421
00:13:53,053 --> 00:13:54,082
- I pressed the button.
- He pressed it.

422
00:13:54,083 --> 00:13:56,093
Min Jun, how many votes did you get?

423
00:13:56,253 --> 00:13:57,953
I got 24 votes.

424
00:13:58,353 --> 00:13:59,522
- You got many votes.
- Yeong Cheol and I...

425
00:13:59,523 --> 00:14:00,722
were in the group that could be eliminated.

426
00:14:00,723 --> 00:14:01,963
- That's right.
- You could be eliminated?

427
00:14:02,433 --> 00:14:04,563
Without knowing how I felt, Yeong Cheol came to me and said,

428
00:14:05,063 --> 00:14:08,103
"Hey, how about we work as a group called Eliminated Boys?"

429
00:14:08,203 --> 00:14:10,733
My gosh. It's getting even worse.

430
00:14:10,833 --> 00:14:13,802
- He was absolutely overbearing...
- It'd be a group with four members.

431
00:14:13,803 --> 00:14:15,972
- Had Min Jung gained 25 votes, - There were 4 of us.

432
00:14:15,973 --> 00:14:17,273
not 24 votes, he wouldn't have been...

433
00:14:17,413 --> 00:14:19,143
- in the bottom four.
- That's right.

434
00:14:19,983 --> 00:14:21,243
- Really?
- That's an important point.

435
00:14:21,343 --> 00:14:23,512
- Really?
- Yeong Cheol is at fault.

436
00:14:23,513 --> 00:14:25,382
- Can we please stop inviting...
- His work life has been too smooth.

437
00:14:25,383 --> 00:14:26,752
those who appeared on "The King of Active Trot Singers?"

438
00:14:26,753 --> 00:14:29,322
- I don't want them on this show.
- I heard Hwanhee came here too.

439
00:14:29,323 --> 00:14:31,492
Yes, Hwanhee came here too. I want no one from the show to come.

440
00:14:31,493 --> 00:14:33,262
- So many people suffered damage.
- Today,

441
00:14:33,263 --> 00:14:34,922
- we'll evaluate you fairly.
- Great.

442
00:14:34,923 --> 00:14:37,233
- So bring me your transfer form.
- Okay.

443
00:14:37,433 --> 00:14:38,592
We'll press the button.

444
00:14:38,593 --> 00:14:39,803
We'll evaluate them properly.

445
00:14:40,263 --> 00:14:42,162
- Today, I will submit...
- We can't just skip it.

446
00:14:42,163 --> 00:14:44,372
- our transfer form.
- What changed your life was...

447
00:14:44,373 --> 00:14:45,632
"Mean Person."

448
00:14:45,633 --> 00:14:47,642
- One, two, three, four.
- Pull it closely.

449
00:14:47,643 --> 00:14:50,272
(Are you leaving me when I still love you?)

450
00:14:50,273 --> 00:14:51,273
What kind of person?

451
00:14:51,274 --> 00:14:52,983
(You're a mean person)

452
00:14:54,213 --> 00:14:57,783
(Soo Geun and Chan Won showed the textbook trot-comedy skit.)

453
00:14:58,183 --> 00:14:59,482
(They brought the memory back after 5 years.)

454
00:14:59,483 --> 00:15:00,952
- It was almost six years ago.
- Maybe I have lingering feelings

455
00:15:00,953 --> 00:15:03,223
- Chan Won played along with you.
- Exactly.

456
00:15:03,423 --> 00:15:04,492
Chan Won is great.

457
00:15:04,493 --> 00:15:05,892
The transfer form to Men on a Mission.

458
00:15:05,893 --> 00:15:08,992
Names, SUNMI, Lee Chan Won, and Song Min Jun.

459
00:15:08,993 --> 00:15:11,133
- It's good to see you guys.
- Welcome!

460
00:15:11,163 --> 00:15:12,232
I was very surprised.

461
00:15:12,233 --> 00:15:16,172
The first thing to check out is their peer relations.

462
00:15:16,173 --> 00:15:18,002
They wrote "Wonderful."

463
00:15:18,003 --> 00:15:19,242
- That's SUNMI...
- Wonderful

464
00:15:19,243 --> 00:15:21,402
- "Dad's Youth?"
- Wonderful

465
00:15:21,403 --> 00:15:23,812
- It's Wonder Girls' fan club name.
- Dad's youth

466
00:15:23,813 --> 00:15:25,013
- Oh, Wonder Girls' fan club?
- Wonderful

467
00:15:25,243 --> 00:15:26,342
Mimi Minu knows it correctly.

