1199
00:39:32,693 --> 00:39:35,192
(I'll go my own way.)

1200
00:39:35,193 --> 00:39:36,423
He's good.

1201
00:39:37,493 --> 00:39:41,603
(His dance satisfied the "Star King" guy.)

1202
00:39:43,363 --> 00:39:46,302
(Each movement breaks the beat through every joint.)

1203
00:39:46,303 --> 00:39:47,573
- Gosh, that's it.
- Yes.

1204
00:39:48,973 --> 00:39:50,673
- Gosh, Min Woo.
- That's great.

1205
00:39:50,913 --> 00:39:52,572
- Min Woo, with these things, - That's great.

1206
00:39:52,573 --> 00:39:54,783
Jang Hoon usually watches...

1207
00:39:55,013 --> 00:39:56,782
and says, "Gosh, what is that?"

1208
00:39:56,783 --> 00:39:59,253
But since he knows that you had a hard time,

1209
00:40:00,053 --> 00:40:03,182
- his face looked so touched.
- I was touched.

1210
00:40:03,183 --> 00:40:05,052
Why did that happen?

1211
00:40:05,053 --> 00:40:08,793
- Is that the Nation's Beloved Host?
- Why did you make him dance?

1212
00:40:08,993 --> 00:40:11,192
We watched the YouTube video.

1213
00:40:11,193 --> 00:40:12,733
Why would you make him dance for no reason?

1214
00:40:12,833 --> 00:40:15,133
- Mimi Minu is amazing.
- It really felt like "Star King."

1215
00:40:16,063 --> 00:40:18,232
- I felt bad for him.
- I saw his videos like that.

1216
00:40:18,233 --> 00:40:19,902
Next, it's Min Jun.

1217
00:40:19,903 --> 00:40:22,603
For his recent update, Min Jun wrote...

1218
00:40:22,973 --> 00:40:24,942
"Trot Young Noble."

1219
00:40:24,943 --> 00:40:26,943
There are a lot of people from royalty in trot.

1220
00:40:27,043 --> 00:40:28,742
- Everyone is royalty.
- They are.

1221
00:40:28,743 --> 00:40:30,342
The Trot Hero is Lim Young Woong.

1222
00:40:30,343 --> 00:40:32,982
- Trot Crown Prince, Trot Emperor, - Yes.

1223
00:40:32,983 --> 00:40:34,253
Trot Prince,

1224
00:40:34,383 --> 00:40:35,982
- Trot Young Noble, - There are a lot.

1225
00:40:35,983 --> 00:40:37,082
Trot Aristocrat...

1226
00:40:37,083 --> 00:40:38,452
There are a lot of young nobles.

1227
00:40:38,453 --> 00:40:40,092
- Aren't there a lot of them?
- There are a lot.

1228
00:40:40,093 --> 00:40:42,492
There are a few candidates.

1229
00:40:42,493 --> 00:40:44,133
- Jeong Dong Won.
- Jeong Dong Won.

1230
00:40:44,233 --> 00:40:45,993
- He's one of the young nobles.
- Jin Hae Seong.

1231
00:40:46,293 --> 00:40:47,502
- Jin Hae Seong.
- Jin Hae Seong.

1232
00:40:47,503 --> 00:40:49,132
- Kim Hee Jae.
- Kim Hee Jae.

1233
00:40:49,133 --> 00:40:50,832
- These are the young nobles.
- Right.

1234
00:40:50,833 --> 00:40:52,172
Are you one of the young nobles, Min Jun?

1235
00:40:52,173 --> 00:40:54,203
I'm one of the young nobles or crown princes.

1236
00:40:54,403 --> 00:40:55,542
- "Crown prince?"
- "Crown prince?"

1237
00:40:55,543 --> 00:40:57,003
- Who gave you the crown?
- He is.

1238
00:40:57,173 --> 00:40:58,442
- What about you, Chan Won?
- What about Chan Won?

1239
00:40:58,443 --> 00:40:59,512
- In the trot world.
- Chan Won Trot.

1240
00:40:59,513 --> 00:41:01,883
I'm relatively younger,

1241
00:41:02,083 --> 00:41:03,543
so I'm usually called the "Trot Idol."

1242
00:41:04,613 --> 00:41:06,552
- "Trot Idol?"
- Who decides that?

1243
00:41:06,553 --> 00:41:09,123
- The fans?
- Yes, the fans usually do that.

1244
00:41:09,283 --> 00:41:12,152
Min Ho is the Trot BTS, right?

1245
00:41:12,153 --> 00:41:13,592
- The BTS of Trot.
- The BTS of Trot.

1246
00:41:13,593 --> 00:41:15,493
Before that,

1247
00:41:15,693 --> 00:41:18,792
- Jin Sung was the BTS of Trot, - That's right.

1248
00:41:18,793 --> 00:41:20,633
but Min Ho took over.

1249
00:41:20,763 --> 00:41:21,862
The guy who sang "At Andong Station?"

1250
00:41:21,863 --> 00:41:25,402
Yes, that guy. He called himself...

1251
00:41:25,403 --> 00:41:28,242
- the "BTS of Trot."
- Isn't he too much older for that?

1252
00:41:28,243 --> 00:41:30,713
He cleanly backed out after Min Ho appeared.

1253
00:41:31,973 --> 00:41:34,982
I heard that the young noble ran away from the royal family.

1254
00:41:34,983 --> 00:41:36,143
- Why?
- You're right.

1255
00:41:36,443 --> 00:41:38,052
I did run away.

1256
00:41:38,053 --> 00:41:40,083
- I used to play soccer, - You did?

1257
00:41:40,283 --> 00:41:42,583
but after I quit, I went to engineering school.

1258
00:41:42,823 --> 00:41:44,753
- You did?
- Until how old did you play?

1259
00:41:44,923 --> 00:41:46,052
Until I was in high school.

1260
00:41:46,053 --> 00:41:48,022
Ever since I was in the first grade, when I was eight years old.

1261
00:41:48,023 --> 00:41:50,862
You started studying again when you were a freshman in high school?

1262
00:41:50,863 --> 00:41:52,732
So I went to engineering school, and...

1263
00:41:52,733 --> 00:41:53,833
- It's hard.
- Yes.

1264
00:41:54,063 --> 00:41:56,603
I didn't know what I was doing there.

1265
00:41:57,263 --> 00:41:59,532
And I liked to sing at that time.

1266
00:41:59,533 --> 00:42:02,173
So I just dropped out...

1267
00:42:03,203 --> 00:42:05,772
and ran away to Seoul without even telling my family,

1268
00:42:05,773 --> 00:42:06,913
with just a bag.

1269
00:42:07,443 --> 00:42:09,583
I just said I'd manage rent with part-time jobs...

1270
00:42:09,783 --> 00:42:10,853
and try to sing.

1271
00:42:11,083 --> 00:42:14,822
So I attended trot contests while working part-time jobs.

1272
00:42:14,823 --> 00:42:16,023
Did you start singing trot from the beginning?

1273
00:42:16,253 --> 00:42:17,892
I used to love ballads.

1274
00:42:17,893 --> 00:42:21,323
But people would say I'm not a good singer with ballads.

1275
00:42:21,823 --> 00:42:23,193
- I'm sure you must have been bad.
- So...

1276
00:42:23,593 --> 00:42:25,192
It could be, since you were young.

1277
00:42:25,193 --> 00:42:28,563
- Yes, I was bad.
- Soo Geun, you're correct.

1278
00:42:28,963 --> 00:42:31,303
It's such a good thing he's singing trot.

1279
00:42:32,573 --> 00:42:35,642
Did people say you were bad when you were singing ballad songs?

1280
00:42:35,643 --> 00:42:37,973
Most of them wouldn't look at me.

1281
00:42:39,113 --> 00:42:40,983
Why is that so?

1282
00:42:41,383 --> 00:42:43,583
But when I went to trot contests, I kept winning first place.

1283
00:42:44,453 --> 00:42:45,852
You must be better at it.

1284
00:42:45,853 --> 00:42:47,652
People would clap and say that I'm good...

1285
00:42:47,653 --> 00:42:49,083
- whenever I sang trot, - That happens.

1286
00:42:49,523 --> 00:42:50,953
so I thought it was the road that I should take,

1287
00:42:51,053 --> 00:42:52,893
and now, I'm still singing trot.

1288
00:42:53,623 --> 00:42:55,822
- Do your parents support you now?
- Of course.

1289
00:42:55,823 --> 00:42:57,992
After I had my debut, they loved it.

1290
00:42:57,993 --> 00:43:01,202
- That's a relief.
- As if they had become myself,

1291
00:43:01,203 --> 00:43:02,862
they loved it so much.

1292
00:43:02,863 --> 00:43:03,863
(My parents love it the most.)

1293
00:43:04,103 --> 00:43:09,603
(Min Jun is loved for doing the music that he loves.)

1294
00:43:10,043 --> 00:43:12,343
On the next line,

1295
00:43:12,513 --> 00:43:14,613
it says, "Idol versus trot singer."

1296
00:43:14,943 --> 00:43:17,812
You are all solo artists, but your genres are different.

1297
00:43:17,813 --> 00:43:19,112
- Yes.
- SUNMI does dance music.

1298
00:43:19,113 --> 00:43:20,853
If the genre is different,

1299
00:43:21,053 --> 00:43:23,052
does the way you treat your fans differ as well?

1300
00:43:23,053 --> 00:43:24,452
- I'm so curious.
- It's very different.

1301
00:43:24,453 --> 00:43:25,893
- Sure.
- It's very different.

1302
00:43:26,023 --> 00:43:27,052
How is it for idols?

1303
00:43:27,053 --> 00:43:30,593
For idols, the fans love it when I act cute.

1304
00:43:30,793 --> 00:43:33,993
To be honest, I'm usually not the affectionate type.

1305
00:43:34,333 --> 00:43:37,032
But in front of the fans, I get really affectionate.

1306
00:43:37,033 --> 00:43:38,672
- It comes out naturally, right?
- Yes.

1307
00:43:38,673 --> 00:43:39,872
- Since the fans like it?
- Yes.

1308
00:43:39,873 --> 00:43:43,273
So even when I take pictures with my fans,

1309
00:43:43,473 --> 00:43:45,573
I get really close...

1310
00:43:45,743 --> 00:43:48,283
- And take pictures?
- and go like this to them.

1311
00:43:48,443 --> 00:43:49,443
Then...

1312
00:43:50,083 --> 00:43:51,853
- You get that close?
- Gosh.

1313
00:43:52,183 --> 00:43:54,822
Shin Dong, let's learn from that.

1314
00:43:54,823 --> 00:43:56,852
- Is it okay to do that?
- Super Junior should do that,

1315
00:43:56,853 --> 00:43:58,022
- Yes, you're an idol.
- We should.

1316
00:43:58,023 --> 00:43:59,752
If we go like that, since we're too close now,

1317
00:43:59,753 --> 00:44:02,593
they will go, "What's wrong with you today?"

1318
00:44:02,723 --> 00:44:04,062
Is it different for trot fans?

1319
00:44:04,063 --> 00:44:05,393
- It's very different.
- How?

1320
00:44:05,633 --> 00:44:09,063
Recently, I went to KBS as a special MC...

1321
00:44:09,833 --> 00:44:12,332
- for "Music Bank."
- That's right.

1322
00:44:12,333 --> 00:44:14,372
For the other shows that I'm currently doing,

1323
00:44:14,373 --> 00:44:15,772
like "Immortal Songs" or "Special Reporter 25 Hours", I say,

1324
00:44:15,773 --> 00:44:18,313
"Immortal Songs will begin now!"

1325
00:44:18,573 --> 00:44:20,143
"Let's watch the video!"

1326
00:44:20,913 --> 00:44:22,383
- "Music Bank."
- But with "Music Bank", it's...

1327
00:44:23,083 --> 00:44:24,783
"Out with a new concept,"

1328
00:44:25,313 --> 00:44:27,552
"it's LE SSERAFIM."

1329
00:44:27,553 --> 00:44:28,782
- "Welcome."
- Yes.

1330
00:44:28,783 --> 00:44:30,322
"Just wait a minute." I had to go like that.

1331
00:44:30,323 --> 00:44:31,923
"Just wait a minute."

1332
00:44:33,393 --> 00:44:35,393
With the shows that I usually do,

1333
00:44:35,893 --> 00:44:38,432
I say, "It will be revealed soon. Please wait a minute."

1334
00:44:38,433 --> 00:44:40,933
- "Just wait a minute."
- "Just wait a minute."

1335
00:44:41,163 --> 00:44:43,603
- "Just wait a minute."
- That's so different.

1336
00:44:44,063 --> 00:44:45,802
- They make it like a conversation.
- And for us...

1337
00:44:45,803 --> 00:44:47,772
At "Music Bank,"

1338
00:44:47,773 --> 00:44:49,602
- you say, "Music, start."
- Yes.

1339
00:44:49,603 --> 00:44:51,712
We say, "Music, please."

1340
00:44:51,713 --> 00:44:54,072
Because Chan Won grew up watching "Star King."

1341
00:44:54,073 --> 00:44:55,143
Yes.

1342
00:44:55,613 --> 00:44:58,853
Ho Dong would go, "Music Bank."

1343
00:44:59,813 --> 00:45:01,653
No one would watch.

1344
00:45:01,923 --> 00:45:04,552
- That's right.
- "We need your warm applause."

1345
00:45:04,553 --> 00:45:06,092
"Music."

1346
00:45:06,093 --> 00:45:08,423
"You can't do that. It's not just any bank."

1347
00:45:08,693 --> 00:45:10,493
"It's Music Bank." He would say that.

1348
00:45:10,693 --> 00:45:12,893
You need to open it like this.

1349
00:45:12,993 --> 00:45:14,502
- Goodness.
- I realized that...

1350
00:45:14,503 --> 00:45:17,903
the main difference is the way we call them.

1351
00:45:18,073 --> 00:45:20,073
- The way you call them.
- Since the age is different.

1352
00:45:20,633 --> 00:45:22,873
We don't see those under 50 as women.

1353
00:45:24,413 --> 00:45:26,673
- Those under 50 aren't women.
- That's a big one.

1354
00:45:26,913 --> 00:45:28,482
You have the elder fans.

1355
00:45:28,483 --> 00:45:29,542
- That's right.
- That's crazy.

1356
00:45:29,543 --> 00:45:31,182
- Only the older women.
- They go only after them.

1357
00:45:31,183 --> 00:45:32,352
Only those over 50.

1358
00:45:32,353 --> 00:45:35,753
Those in their 30s or 40s are like babies.

1359
00:45:36,323 --> 00:45:37,383
They are babies?

1360
00:45:37,523 --> 00:45:39,992
We really don't see those under 50 as women.

1361
00:45:39,993 --> 00:45:42,123
But when they come, for example,

1362
00:45:42,393 --> 00:45:43,563
they are my mother's age,

1363
00:45:43,663 --> 00:45:45,662
- Yes.
- and those who are even older...

1364
00:45:45,663 --> 00:45:47,032
- could be my grandmother's age.
- Sure.

1365
00:45:47,033 --> 00:45:49,032
Then, usually, in normal situations,

1366
00:45:49,033 --> 00:45:51,602
we would call them "ma'am" or "madam."

1367
00:45:51,603 --> 00:45:53,472
- But they hate it when we do that.
- They don't like it.

1368
00:45:53,473 --> 00:45:55,272
- They feel so offended.
- Do you need to call their names?

1369
00:45:55,273 --> 00:45:57,272
We were showing respect, but they don't like it?

1370
00:45:57,273 --> 00:45:58,273
Then what should we call them?

1371
00:45:58,473 --> 00:45:59,512
- What do you say?
- "Older sister?"

1372
00:45:59,513 --> 00:46:01,342
Don't you have to call their name? "Mal Ja."

1373
00:46:01,343 --> 00:46:02,713
- Correct.
- Sure.

1374
00:46:03,343 --> 00:46:05,013
"Hi there, Gyeong Sook, born in 1944."

1375
00:46:06,013 --> 00:46:07,212
- That's correct.
- Really?

1376
00:46:07,213 --> 00:46:08,982
Soo Geun, you are correct.

1377
00:46:08,983 --> 00:46:10,952
We do that sometimes.

1378
00:46:10,953 --> 00:46:12,023
"Born in 1944?"

1379
00:46:12,423 --> 00:46:14,762
- "Born in 1944?"
- "Gyeong Sook, born in 1944."

1380
00:46:14,763 --> 00:46:16,323
- That's so funny.
- We...

1381
00:46:16,863 --> 00:46:19,762
We actually get messages on our social media.

1382
00:46:19,763 --> 00:46:21,132
They call us "darling," but...

1383
00:46:21,133 --> 00:46:25,503
"I enjoyed your performance today, my darling."

1384
00:46:25,673 --> 00:46:26,972
- The sentence structure.
- The old style.

1385
00:46:26,973 --> 00:46:29,442
- It's the old spelling.
- They use the old words.

1386
00:46:29,443 --> 00:46:31,612
I think, "She called me darling, though."

1387
00:46:31,613 --> 00:46:33,413
So when I see their profile picture,

1388
00:46:33,473 --> 00:46:35,812
she's standing like this in the flower field.

1389
00:46:35,813 --> 00:46:37,283
With her granddaughter in her arms.

1390
00:46:37,753 --> 00:46:38,882
Most of them are like that.

1391
00:46:38,883 --> 00:46:40,213
- They are all young girls inside.
- Yes.

1392
00:46:40,313 --> 00:46:42,282
Is there a memorable fan you met at the rest stop?

1393
00:46:42,283 --> 00:46:44,553
- I still remember where it was.
- Okay.

1394
00:46:44,793 --> 00:46:46,622
I was going past Geumsan, South Chungcheong Province,

1395
00:46:46,623 --> 00:46:48,593
- and Geumsan is known for ginseng.
- That's right.

1396
00:46:48,763 --> 00:46:51,762
So the name of the rest stop is "Geumsan Ginseng Land Rest Stop."

1397
00:46:51,763 --> 00:46:52,763
- I remember it.
- That's right.

1398
00:46:52,764 --> 00:46:53,892
Yes, it's Ginseng Land.

1399
00:46:53,893 --> 00:46:55,262
There's a Ginseng Land Rest Stop.

1400
00:46:55,263 --> 00:46:57,202
But usually, when I go to the restroom,

1401
00:46:57,203 --> 00:46:58,402
it's a bit embarrassing if someone recognizes me.

1402
00:46:58,403 --> 00:47:00,772
- Right. You wear a hat.
- So I usually wear a hat.

1403
00:47:00,773 --> 00:47:02,403
But there was no one there.

1404
00:47:02,503 --> 00:47:05,613
So I went to the bathroom, and I relieved myself,

1405
00:47:05,943 --> 00:47:07,442
and when I came out,

1406
00:47:07,443 --> 00:47:09,713
an elderly man saw me and said,

1407
00:47:10,243 --> 00:47:12,382
"Aren't you Lee Chan Won?"

1408
00:47:12,383 --> 00:47:14,323
He was about 70 years old.

1409
00:47:14,553 --> 00:47:15,782
"Aren't you Lee Chan Won?"

1410
00:47:15,783 --> 00:47:17,482
"Gosh, I'm also from Daegu."

1411
00:47:17,483 --> 00:47:19,593
"It's so nice to meet someone from the same hometown."

1412
00:47:19,693 --> 00:47:21,762
"I was always supporting you."

1413
00:47:21,763 --> 00:47:22,792
"Let's shake hands."

1414
00:47:22,793 --> 00:47:24,632
So I said, "Thank you."

1415
00:47:24,633 --> 00:47:26,533
"Enjoy your time," and was about to go, but he said,

1416
00:47:26,693 --> 00:47:29,563
"Let me poop where Lee Chan Won pooped."

1417
00:47:31,303 --> 00:47:32,473
I'm serious.

1418
00:47:33,703 --> 00:47:35,302
(There's a reason he couldn't forget that time.)

1419
00:47:35,303 --> 00:47:36,842
- That's so good.
- Goodness.

1420
00:47:36,843 --> 00:47:38,142
- That's so funny.
- Gosh.

1421
00:47:38,143 --> 00:47:40,843
- Gosh.
- Ho Dong, is he a Strong Heart?

1422
00:47:41,243 --> 00:47:42,313
Strong Heart?

1423
00:47:42,343 --> 00:47:44,182
- You got it!
- I got it!

1424
00:47:44,183 --> 00:47:45,382
(Chan Won got it!)

1425
00:47:45,383 --> 00:47:46,783
- Gosh.
- That's amazing.

1426
00:47:46,913 --> 00:47:48,083
That's a Strong Heart.

1427
00:47:48,353 --> 00:47:49,722
It's true, though.

1428
00:47:49,723 --> 00:47:51,392
- That's amazing.
- It's true.

1429
00:47:51,393 --> 00:47:53,893
Lastly, it's the Question Aptitude Test.

1430
00:47:54,323 --> 00:47:57,422
It's something we're promoting.

1431
00:47:57,423 --> 00:48:00,193
- I'm curious.
- It's "Ask Me."

1432
00:48:00,633 --> 00:48:02,662
Each of the students prepared a question...

1433
00:48:02,663 --> 00:48:05,202
that they would like to ask the transfer students.

1434
00:48:05,203 --> 00:48:06,533
- I will go first.
- Okay.

1435
00:48:06,873 --> 00:48:07,972
My question.

1436
00:48:07,973 --> 00:48:10,673
It's the same question for all three of you.

1437
00:48:11,073 --> 00:48:13,112
- If you could be reborn, - Yes?

1438
